items.name: Sone Miyuki
items.description:
Trained to resemble official artstyle.

I've not done extensive testing but some issues (varies per model and strength):

  • her dress shirt seems to have baked itself in - sometimes the collar, sleeves or center frills will appear unprompted

  • the white spots on her hair might appear in too large quantities

The DAdapt version seems slightly less accurate to the style/more generic and I think it avoids these issues better, so use that one if you run into them too often and lowering strength doesn't help.
Miyuki-2000 is old, but included it as it is the one I used for my pixiv pictures.

When prompting for "crazy eyes", putting "red eyes" in negatives might help, but unsure.

Prompts used for her dress shirt

  • collared dress, white dress, dress, center frills, belt, long sleeves

Prompts used for cardigan/school uniform

  • yellow cardigan, neckerchief, serafuku, school uniform, pleated skirt, buttons, skirt, sailor collar, miniskirt

You probably don't need all of them - the first tag should be enough.

Prompts for the red scenery and sky

  • red theme, outdoors, no humans, building, scenery, chain-link fence, surreal, monochrome, rooftop, cloudy sky, red sky

Same as above, "red theme", "monochrome" and "surreal" should be enough, include sky in either positive or negative as required.

Feel free to contact me if you want the dataset or for any other purpose.

items.name: UnderPlayer
items.description:
Hi guys. This is my first time posting a LoRA on Civitai. I'm not that good at making a LoRA either so I apologize if this model does not generate top quality images. I really liked Undertale and this AU in general so that is why I made this. This model is supposed to generate images of Player from the UnderPlayer AU made by Yunan (é±¼è…©).

Limitations

This LoRA model is not perfect and it has some limitations that Iâ€™m aware of. Some of them are:

  • The model sometimes generates a white part of the dress/sweater at the bottom part instead of remembering that the white is only for the inside.

  • The model sometimes generates extra or fewer stripes on the dress/sweater.

  • The model sometimes generates a regular human skin tone instead of a gray-ish one.

  • The model sometimes generates multiple views of Player in one image.

  • Sometimes like to combine uncolored and colored sclera which does not end well.

  • This LoRA generates colored (black) scleras better than regular white ones.

Settings:

To generate images using my LoRA model, I recommend you use the following settings:

  • Use a 2D style checkpoint instead of a semi-realistic or realistic one.

  • Use a higher CFG scale like 8.5+.

  • For the prompt, along with the trigger words, I recommend you use: red hair, short hair, solo, pantyhose, black boots, (red striped dress), (striped sweater), turtleneck. And then whatever else you want.

  • For the negative prompt, I recommend you use: text, title, logo, signature, watermark, multiple views, white dress, cropped, out of frame, arms behind back, jpeg artifacts, inaccurate eyes, bad hands. And also things like AuroraNegative.


When generating the preview images I used ColorMagination and I recommend you use it if you want to try this LoRa since it generates good images. To make this LoRA I used this resource. I hope you like this and please tell me any feedback or suggestions you might have so I can improve. Thank you for reading all of this.

Like the work I do and want to help support me? Buy me a coffee! â˜•ï¸ğŸ«¶ğŸ¼

Meet ProtoVision XL! This model is my "Bob Ross" model, a happy accident that happened when I goofed up some merge settings on my DynaVision XL model and stumbled upon some magic.

So what is ProtoVisionXL? At its core it's a custom built version of NightVision XL, which I then pile multiple fabulous LORAs on top of to create a unique look.

Like all of my other models, merges, embeds and tools, ProtoVisionXL is designed to be easy to use and excels with simple prompts, but is very coherent and can build fabulous scenes with exquisite detail.

ProtoVisionXL is a portrait model, it favors showing human subjects. That's not to say you can't get other art styles, creatures, landscapes and objects out of it, as it's still SDXL at its core and is very capable.

WARNING - DO NOT USE SDXL REFINER WITH PROTOVISION XL

The SDXL refiner is incompatible and you will have reduced quality output if you try to use the base model refiner with ProtoVision XL.

What is ExÅ«berantia?

ExÅ«berantia is a model that came about after I found a lora called "3D Rendering Style", I really liked the way it looked so first tried to just merged it with Aurora but it didn't have that look I had in my mind, so I created a completely new model merge and tried various versions but after 18 beta versions and comparing them all I decided on the one I liked most and decided to release it in beta form. There are a few tweaks and issues to fix, mainly hands and fingers but that will come in time.

What is V0.9?

There's a problem: Even with simple prompts like silver hair or red eyes, it generates a female character.

Trained on SD 1.5
Triggers with Astarion


To improve results recommended:
VAE sd-vae-ft-mse-original
Negative embedding for ChilloutMix
even better result with:
ControlNet with Preprocessor: reference_only

Works well with ChilloutMix, NED,
I tried some other Checkpoints Experience, RPG results was bad


How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight according to the instructions (by default it's :1)

Now you can generate not only a portrait.

Problems:

  • It can't recognize his pants correctly D:

Better result with:
ControlNet with Preprocessor: reference_only with this IMAGE or try any other

items.name: Liney4ka - Lined Paper
items.description:
Hi there! I've decided to release another creative LoRa model. It's quite an unusual approach we have here. This model is meant for generating sketches on lined pages. Yes, specifically lined pages, like those in notebooks. You can try making sketches on this kind of paper. I'll provide some examples, and you can use them as a reference for your own work. I'll continue improving the model and enhancing its quality in the future. Currently, the models respond differently to LoRa values, so it's just a trial and experiment phase. Perhaps you have suggestions or advice, or maybe you can find some useful tips and tricks. I'd appreciate any positive feedback from you. â¤

  • CFG Scale - 2-7, Clip skip: 1,( may be 2), any Sampler

  • <lora:Liney4ka:0.9> ( 0.5 >1)

items.name: Aurora
items.description:
What is Aurora?

Aurora was made to counterbalance the realism that Euclid provided, giving you a model that can go from creating cartoons to anime and even creating semi-realistic images. As you can see from the preview image it does have a lot more freedom and artistic expression than Euclid. So please enjoy and have fun.

What is Aurora V3?

V3 is an updated version of Aurora which adds some more freedom to what V2 offered. I added an anime-style model, and a cartoon-style model and added Dreamshaper 8 to the mix to complement Dreamshaper 6 which was included in V2. V1 was a side project which was only really made for cartoon/anime-type images and to see what I could do outside of the realms of realism. V2 expanded on that as V1 was quite limited and to be honest, rubbish. V2 was now able to cover pixel art and semi-realistic images as well as pretty much everything between to an extent. V3 expands on this further and also provides a better overall image, but does sort of strays away from overall cartoon/anime unless prompted to do so.

items.name: Anato Finnstark Style
items.description:
This is my attempt at recreating the painting style of Anato Finnstark. This model works great at a strength 0.65-0.8 but if you plan to combine this lora with another style lora, then you should lower the strength down to 0.5-0.7. It also works best at landscape resolution.

If you wanna try the unique style i have been getting by using the Jakub Rozalski lora together with this lora, then i recommend to have the Anato Finnstark lora at strength 0.5-0.6 and the Jakub Rozalski lora at 0.35

If you use higher strengths you will start to lose control over your prompts. I also strongly recommend to use these loras together:

LowRA

epi_noiseoffset

Add More Details

You should not use LowRA and epi_noiseoffset together since they both create a similar effect.

Also also try using the loras without much prompting. They usually default to a person standing in a field or just scenery images. Just keep your quality prompts and test it out. Works great with adding different color themes such as:

Yellow: (yellow theme)

Violet: (violet theme)

Green: (green theme)

Red: (red theme)

Blue: (blue theme)

Or try mixing two themes with:

[red theme:violet theme:0.5] this will generate a red theme the first 50% steps and then change over to a violet theme for the rest 50% steps.
